Czech Cabinet Plans New State Treasury System, Hospodarske Says

-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 
2011-03-01T07:10:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/czech-cabinet-plans-new-state-treasury-system-hospodarske-says.html
The Czech  Finance Ministry  plans to
spend about 5 billion koruna ($284 million) on a new treasury
system to better manage state cash flow,  Hospodarske Noviny 
reported, citing Deputy Finance Minister Zdenek Zajicek.  The Finance Ministry may use the new treasury system for
the first time to prepare the 2013 state budget, the newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
 placa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  